    <h1>Do immigrant students underperform? PISA 2022 data by country</h1>
    <p class="intro">OECD PISA 2022 data shows a raw score gap of −29 points between immigrant-background and native-born students. After controlling for socioeconomic status, this narrows to −5 points — meaning 83% of the gap is explained by socioeconomic factors.</p>
    <div class="lang-switch"><a href="/faq/pisa-enfants-immigres/">🌐 日本語版</a></div>
  </div>

